  "narrative": {
    "intro": "Federal contract obligations for NAICS 334511 totaled $8.9B in FY2026 to date, with 5,866 awards and an average award size of $1.5M. Obligations are down 51.7% year over year. Recent fiscal-year totals show a peak in FY25 at $18.4B and a stepwise decline to the current-year partial total of $8.9B. The Department of Defense dominates buying, with $6.9B in obligations, followed by the Department of Transportation at $1B and the Department of Homeland Security at $799M. The vendor landscape is concentrated among large systems contractors, led by RAYTHEON COMPANY at $838M and LOCKHEED MARTIN CORPORATION at $667M, with multiple other prime awards to RAYTHEON COMPANY and NORTHROP GRUMMAN SYSTEMS CORPORATION. Smaller agency buyers and niche vendors appear in the lower tens of millions, including the Department of Energy at $34.4M and UNDERSEA SENSOR SYSTEMS, INC. at $241M. These figures reflect partial fiscal-year activity and the current composition of obligations across buyers and vendors in FY2026 to date.",
    "sections": [
      {
        "heading": "How large is the FY2026 federal market for NAICS 334511?",
        "body": "The FY2026 to date federal market for NAICS 334511 is $8.9B in obligations. That total comprises 5,866 awards with an average award size of $1.5M and is down 51.7% year over year. Fiscal-year history shows prior totals of $13.2B in FY21, $13.9B in FY22, $17B in FY23, $17.1B in FY24, and $18.4B in FY25."
      },
      {
        "heading": "Who are the primary buyers and suppliers in FY2026 to date?",
        "body": "The Department of Defense is the largest buyer with $6.9B in obligations, followed by the Department of Transportation at $1B and the Department of Homeland Security at $799M. Top suppliers include RAYTHEON COMPANY at $838M and LOCKHEED MARTIN CORPORATION at $667M, with additional major awards to RAYTHEON COMPANY and NORTHROP GRUMMAN SYSTEMS CORPORATION and others down the list."
      }
